# Firmware Rules

## Watchdog Safety
- Never feed the watchdog during blocking waits or delays - it exists to catch blocking situations
- Operations exceeding the 256ms watchdog timeout must use non-blocking state machine patterns

## Non-Blocking Code
- Avoid blocking calls in the main loop: no `Delay_ms()` in operational code, no `while` loops waiting on hardware state
- Use state machine patterns for multi-step operations with timeout tracking
- Use timestamp comparison (`Milliseconds()`) instead of blocking delays

## Main Loop
- Must complete within 256ms (watchdog timeout), target <10ms for responsive telemetry
- All sub-operations must be non-blocking
